(c) Zn being more reactive than Ag and Au , displaces them.
$$
\begin{aligned}
4 \mathrm{Ag}+8 \mathrm{NaCN}+2 \mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{O}+ & \mathrm{O}_{2} \xrightarrow{\text { Leaching }} \\
4 \mathrm{Na}\left[\mathrm{Ag}(\mathrm{CN})_{2}\right]+4 \mathrm{NaOH} & \text { Soluble Sodium dicyanoargentate (I) }
\end{aligned}
$$
Soluble cyanide compound can be treated with Zn to give metal by displacement.
